resources.description:
This request also contains an example response. You can view it in the panel on the right hand side.

```response
{
  "ok": true,
  "data": [
    {
      "name": "Insomnia",
      "description": "REST client for humans"
    },
    {
      "name": "Insomnia Documenter",
      "description": "Documentation generator for Insomnia"
    }
  ]
}
```

In order to generate an example response block, you must enclose it between a markdown code block with `response` language tag.

You can specify multiple example responses -- now with status codes! Instead of using just `response` for language tag you can write `response:200`.

```response:200
{
  "ok": true,
  "token": "123abc"
}
```

```response:400
{
  "ok": false,
  "error": "Username or password not provided."
}
```

```response:401
{
  "ok": false,
  "error": "Incorrect username and/or password."
}
```

